retrofit:ReleaseGateBrokenForWeeks a retrofit:SPOF ;
    rdfs:label "release.yml audit gate -- RESOLVED: full workflow observed genuinely green end to end, first time in this SPOF's history" ;
    retrofit:standing "Accepted" ;
    retrofit:affects retrofit:ReleasePath ;
    retrofit:evidence "RESOLVED (root cause + fix), NOT YET CI-CONFIRMED, re-verified 2026-07-21: commit 53961f0ac / merged PR #349 identified the exact gate -- `cargo cicd status audit` hardcoded an OCEL evidence path but `wpm audit` only parses XES, so every release-workflow run refused with a format-mismatch error (confirmed against a real GH Actions run URL in that commit's own message). Live .github/workflows/release.yml now calls `wpm audit \"$XES\"` against the real events.xes sibling file, bypassing the OCEL-hardcoded path -- fix is committed and live. Kept Blocking, not restood Accepted, because that PR's own disclosed standing says a real green release.yml run post-fix is still required before this can claim Proven -- the fix is a workflow-file diff plus local reproduction, not that run. Next action: observe the next real release.yml execution; restand to Accepted only once a genuine green run is observed, not before." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22 "CORRECTING the prior evidence's optimistic 'awaiting confirmation' framing with a real, contradicting observation, per no-overclaiming discipline: the OCEL/XES fix DID land and the format-mismatch failure mode is genuinely gone, but release.yml has NOT gone green -- `gh run list --workflow=release.yml --limit 5` shows 5/5 recent runs on main FAILED (2026-07-21T05:57Z through 2026-07-22T03:44Z), all in the SAME job/step: 'Release Health Check' > 'Process conformance gate (wpm oracle)'. Real log evidence from the most recent run (databaseId 29889224190, 2026-07-22T03:49:24Z): `wpm audit` itself now runs cleanly against real XES evidence (exit 0, confirming the OCEL/XES fix holds) and produces 'Audit Verdict: DECEPTIVE, Fitness Score: 0.0000, Precision Score: 1.0000, Total Traces Audited: 1, Deviating Traces: 1' with the sole sample deviation showing 'trace-0  0.00  M: 0, R: 0' (zero missing/remaining events, yet zero fitness) -- the gate's own bash then greps the lowercased output for 'deceptive' and exits 1 by design ('[REFUSE] DECEPTIVE -- event log does not prove a lawful process happened'). This is a NEW, different blocker from the one PR #349 fixed: a real conformance-checking defect (either in how release.yml's own workflow run generates its events.xes trace, or in the wpm oracle's model/oracle definition for what a 'lawful' release-workflow trace looks like) causing a single-trace audit to score 0 fitness with 0 named problems -- not yet root-caused by this pass (out of scope for CiIntegrationTestsNeverRun's closure; named precisely here rather than left silently unrestood). Standing correctly remains Blocking -- ReleasePath is still not provably working end-to-end." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22b "ADDITIVE, DOES NOT RESOLVE THE DECEPTIVE/FITNESS-0.0 BLOCKER ABOVE: PR #416 (branch fix/release-gate-pin-external-deps, open, not yet merged -- correcting this entry's own earlier 'merged' overclaim) fixed a third, orthogonal problem found while investigating why this gate's apparent root cause kept shifting between sessions -- .github/actions/install-cargo-tools/action.yml installed both cargo-cicd and wasm4pm-cli (wpm) via `cargo install --git ... --branch main`, a floating ref. Since the release-health job's TRUTHFUL/VARIANCE/DECEPTIVE verdict (including the DECEPTIVE/fitness-0.0 result documented directly above) is computed entirely inside these two external, ggen-uncontrolled tools, a floating branch meant that verdict -- and whether the tool even compiled -- could change with zero corresponding ggen-side commit. Now pinned to named commits (cargo-cicd@852a2d965, wasm4pm@98541a5ff); each install reproduced successfully from a scratch CARGO_HOME/--root outside CI before pushing. This does NOT fix the DECEPTIVE verdict itself -- that logic lives in wasm4pm's own fitness/precision algorithms, out of bounds per this repo's own Process Intelligence Boundary rule (CLAUDE.md). What it buys: the DECEPTIVE/fitness-0.0 finding above is now reproducible against a fixed, named external commit instead of 'whatever wasm4pm@main happens to be during this workflow run' -- the actual prerequisite for the real root-cause work in the next update." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22c "THE DECEPTIVE/FITNESS-0.0 BLOCKER ABOVE IS NOW ROOT-CAUSED AND FIXED (PR #419, branch fix/release-gate-degenerate-trace, open, not yet merged): using the pinned cargo-cicd@852a2d965/wasm4pm@98541a5ff revs from PR #416, reproduced the exact DECEPTIVE/0.0000/M:0,R:0 shape locally by running only `cargo cicd workspace doctor` in a scratch evidence dir. Root cause: that single command emits exactly ONE declared-model activity event ('workspace:doctor' complete) into events.xes -- cargo-cicd's evidence writer intentionally drops 'start' lifecycle events before building the XES (seanchatmangpt/cargo-cicd src/evidence.rs::emit_xes_impl, its own comment: 'they duplicate activity names and corrupt token replay fitness'). `wpm audit` self-discovers a Petri net/directly-follows graph FROM THAT SAME LOG and token-replays it against itself -- with only 1 event, the discovered model has zero real directly-follows edges, only a synthetic sink-consume transition whose postset is empty, so `produced` ends up exactly 0 while `consumed` is nonzero. wasm4pm's compute_fitness (wasm4pm/src/simd_token_replay.rs:375-384) only guards the case where BOTH consumed AND produced are 0 -- this asymmetric zero falls through to a 0.0/0.0 division, producing NaN, which serializes to JSON null and gets silently displayed as a literal '0.0000'/'M: 0, R: 0' by wpm-cli's own `.unwrap_or(0.0)` printer (wasm4pm-cli src/commands/audit.rs). Confirmed NOT a genuine conformance violation: running 3 more of cargo-cicd's own already-declared, read-only, side-effect-free diagnostic activities (status show / target show / test changed) in the SAME evidence session before the audit turns the trace into a real multi-activity one, and the identical `wpm audit` verdict flips to TRUTHFUL, Fitness 1.0000, Precision 1.0000, 1/1 fitting traces. Also ran the full step-chain reproduction (exact bash from both release.yml steps, copy-run in sequence): FINAL EXIT CODE 0. `test changed`'s git-diff-against-origin/main confirmed safe under this job's shallow, tag-only checkout (fetch-depth: 1, no origin/main ref present) by reading ChangedFileDetector::changed_rs_files directly -- it falls back to an empty diff on any git-command failure rather than erroring, and TestChangedVerb::run always emits a PASS event regardless of what it finds. `status audit` (separate, already-known OCEL-hardcoded-path bug) and `target prune`/`publish run` (destructive/release-adjacent) are deliberately excluded from the fix. This does not touch wasm4pm/cargo-cicd's own algorithm code, per the Process Intelligence Boundary rule -- it only runs more of the SAME evidence-emitting commands this workflow already trusted. Standing correctly remains Blocking: all three fixes (#349 merged and live, #416 and #419 open) are real and independently verified by local reproduction, but zero of them has yet been confirmed by an actual green release.yml run -- this repo's release.yml only triggers on tag push or workflow_dispatch, not on PR CI, so that confirmation can only come from the next real tagged release or a manual workflow_dispatch. Next action: after #416/#419 merge, trigger or await the next real release.yml run; restand to Accepted only once it is observed green." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22d "#416 AND #419 BOTH MERGED; A REAL RELEASE.YML RUN CONFIRMS THE DECEPTIVE FIX HOLDS, THEN EXPOSES A NEW, DISTINCT, PREVIOUSLY-UNREACHABLE FAILURE: run 29911316089 (2026-07-22T10:17Z, headSha 2f85678b8, after both merges) shows job 'Release Health Check' -- SUCCESS. The DECEPTIVE-verdict blocker documented in evidenceUpdate2026_07_22/b/c is genuinely resolved; this is the first real evidence, not another local reproduction. But the workflow OVERALL still reports failure: 'Build Release' (all 4 platform targets) and every 'Cross-Host Repro' leg failed, each with the SAME error -- `error: could not execute process 'sccache ... rustc -vV' (never executed) ... No such file or directory`. Root cause (see PR #426, branch fix/release-build-job-missing-setup): both jobs used a bespoke dtolnay/rust-toolchain step (`toolchain: stable`, no sibling-repo provisioning, no sccache install) instead of the already-proven ./.github/actions/setup-ggen-build composite action every other CI job uses. Not a new defect -- a latent one, invisible until now because build-release's own `needs: [release-health]` gate blocked it behind the DECEPTIVE bug for as long as that bug existed; fixing evidenceUpdate2026_07_22c's finding is what let this run far enough to hit it for the first time. `toolchain: stable` is independently wrong too: setup-ggen-build's own STEP 2 comment states nightly-2026-06-22 (matching rust-toolchain.toml) is the only channel that compiles this workspace. PR #426 fixes both jobs -- build-release now reuses setup-ggen-build wholesale; build-release-repro gets the same two missing pieces (sibling provisioning + sccache) inlined verbatim rather than the full composite, since that job's entire premise is a truly cold, uncached build and the composite's own caching step would silently undermine that guarantee. Standing correctly remains Blocking: ReleasePath is closer to working than at any point in this SPOF's history (the actual conformance-gate defect is fixed and confirmed by a real run) but still not provably working end-to-end -- PR #426 is open, not yet merged, and its own fix has the same real-run-only verification limit as every fix before it. Next action: merge #426; observe the next real release.yml run; restand to Accepted only once Build Release and Cross-Host Repro are observed green, not merely Release Health Check." ;
    retrofit:evidenceUpdate2026_07_22f "RESTOOD TO ACCEPTED -- THE CONDITION NAMED IN EVERY PRIOR UPDATE IS NOW MET FOR REAL: PR #426 merged, then a real post-fix run (29915682895) surfaced two MORE previously-unreachable bugs (both root-caused and fixed in PR #432, branch fix/release-macos-bash3-compat -- macOS's system bash 3.2.57 has no associative-array support, breaking the sibling-provisioning script on every macOS-hosted job; and a genuinely dead `reqwest` runtime dependency in ggen-cli plus a workspace-wide reqwest spec that never disabled default-features, both compiling in native-tls/openssl-sys unnecessarily and breaking the aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu cross-compile). PR #432 merged 2026-07-22T12:19:41Z; the resulting semantic-release run (29919176631, success) tagged and dispatched a fresh release.yml run, databaseId 29919854272, completed 2026-07-22T12:58:09Z (real GH Actions run, not local reproduction). Every one of its 16 jobs succeeded: Release Health Check; all 4 Build Release targets (x86_64/aarch64 x apple-darwin/unknown-linux-gnu); all 8 Cross-Host Repro replicas (2 independent builds x 4 targets); and, for the first time ever, all 4 Verify Cross-Host Reproducibility jobs actually RAN (never reached in any prior run) and passed, confirming genuine byte-identical reproducibility across independently-provisioned build hosts for every release target. Five real, independently-verified fixes accumulated across this SPOF's history are now all confirmed live and sufficient together: PR #349 (OCEL/XES format-mismatch), PR #416 (dependency pinning), PR #419 (degenerate-trace DECEPTIVE bug), PR #426 (missing build-job setup), PR #432 (macOS bash 3.2 compat + openssl-sys elimination). retrofit:ReleasePath is provably working end-to-end, observed directly, not inferred. No further action required on this SPOF; a future regression would need its own fresh finding, not a reopening of this one." .

